('chk-testops-review', 'ph-ci-cd-testops', 90, 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'TestOps Review Gate', 'Practical checkpoint for CI/CD, TestOps, and Quality Engineering. The learner completes a small diagnostic task or review artifact using CI/CD Basics for QA, GitHub Actions for QA, Jenkins for QA, Quality Gates and records observations that can guide further practice.', 'This checkpoint gives the software quality assurance roadmap a reviewable activity at the end of a technical segment instead of a passive completion checkbox. It does not independently verify mastery.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-ci-cd-testops', 11, 90, 2, 'advanced', 100, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/qa", "visualRole": "checkpoint", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "assessment", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply selected concepts from CI/CD, TestOps, and Quality Engineering to a small practical scenario.", "Explain what worked, what failed, and which signals were used to debug or validate the result.", "Translate the result into a short next-action plan for continued learning."]'::jsonb, '["Complete a small practical task, lab, review exercise, or worked example related to this segment.", "Attach or describe the output, result, or evidence used for review.", "Explain at least one mistake, trade-off, or failure mode encountered during the task.", "Write the next practice action based on the result."]'::jsonb),
('proj-ci-quality-gate', 'ph-ci-cd-testops', 100, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required CI Quality Gate Pipeline', 'Milestone project brief: Build a pipeline that runs API/UI tests, publishes reports/artifacts, enforces thresholds, and documents release signal quality. Build a reviewable data pipeline project that demonstrates the main decisions from CI/CD, TestOps, and Quality Engineering. Expected evidence includes an ingest-transform-load flow, schema or data quality checks, and a run log or lineage note explaining failure handling. Keep scope focused so the result can be completed, checked, and explained.', 'This required milestone project turns the surrounding QA Engineer topics into a concrete artifact. It gives the learner a clearer target, suggested build path, and review evidence without treating completion as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-ci-cd-testops', 11, 100, 6, 'advanced', 100, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/qa","visualRole": "side","projectPurpose": "milestone_practice","projectKind": "data_pipeline","projectScope": "focused_milestone","evidenceRequired": true,"claimLimit": "reviewable_project_evidence_only_not_mastery_or_job_readiness","suggestedSteps": ["define source, target, and transformation rules","implement a reproducible run path","add quality checks and failure notes","document operational assumptions"],"expectedEvidence": ["an ingest-transform-load flow","schema or data quality checks","a run log or lineage note explaining failure handling"],"optionalPractice": false,"milestone": true}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Build a focused CI Quality Gate Pipeline artifact that demonstrates the main concepts from CI/CD, TestOps, and Quality Engineering.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, or workflow decisions used in the project.","Validate the project with appropriate evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, queries, or review notes.","Document setup, usage, limitations, and at least one follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["A repository, notebook, dashboard, write-up, prototype, or configuration artifact is available for review.","The README or project notes state the project goal, setup steps, usage path, and expected output.","The deliverable includes an ingest-transform-load flow, schema or data quality checks, and a run log or lineage note explaining failure handling.","The learner records validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, query results, playtest notes, or manual verification steps.","The review notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."]'::jsonb),
