('chk-ai-qa-review', 'ph-ai-qa', 90, 'checkpoint', 'gate', NULL, NULL, 'AI-Assisted QA Review Gate', 'Review checkpoint for AI-Assisted QA and Modern Testing Workflows. The learner consolidates evidence from AI for Test Case Generation, AI for Automation Assistance, AI-Assisted Test Data Generation, AI-Assisted Log and Failure Analysis, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.', 'This checkpoint acts as a transition gate for the software quality assurance roadmap. It supports reflection and planning; it is not a certification, mastery test, or claim of job readiness.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-ai-qa', 12, 90, 1, 'intermediate', 100, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/qa", "visualRole": "checkpoint", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "gate", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Summarize the main concepts and decisions from AI-Assisted QA and Modern Testing Workflows in practical software quality assurance terms.", "Identify prerequisite gaps, unclear topics, or risks that should be reviewed before moving forward.", "Create a short evidence artifact that links completed roadmap items to what was learned."]'::jsonb, '["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.", "Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.", "Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."]'::jsonb),
('proj-ai-assisted-test-design', 'ph-ai-qa', 100, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required AI-Assisted Test Design Pack', 'Milestone project brief: Use AI to assist with test ideas, edge cases, automation snippets, and failure analysis, then document validation and corrections. Build a reviewable quality engineering artifact that demonstrates the main decisions from AI-Assisted QA and Modern Testing Workflows. Expected evidence includes a test plan or automation suite, sample defects or risk notes, and execution evidence with pass/fail output. Keep scope focused so the result can be completed, checked, and explained.', 'This required milestone project turns the surrounding QA Engineer topics into a concrete artifact. It gives the learner a clearer target, suggested build path, and review evidence without treating completion as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-ai-qa', 12, 100, 5, 'intermediate', 100, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/qa","visualRole": "side","projectPurpose": "milestone_practice","projectKind": "qa_project","projectScope": "focused_milestone","evidenceRequired": true,"claimLimit": "reviewable_project_evidence_only_not_mastery_or_job_readiness","suggestedSteps": ["identify risks and test targets","design manual and/or automated checks","run the checks and capture output","summarize defects and coverage gaps"],"expectedEvidence": ["a test plan or automation suite","sample defects or risk notes","execution evidence with pass/fail output"],"optionalPractice": false,"milestone": true}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Build a focused AI-Assisted Test Design Pack artifact that demonstrates the main concepts from AI-Assisted QA and Modern Testing Workflows.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, or workflow decisions used in the project.","Validate the project with appropriate evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, queries, or review notes.","Document setup, usage, limitations, and at least one follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["A repository, notebook, dashboard, write-up, prototype, or configuration artifact is available for review.","The README or project notes state the project goal, setup steps, usage path, and expected output.","The deliverable includes a test plan or automation suite, sample defects or risk notes, and execution evidence with pass/fail output.","The learner records validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, query results, playtest notes, or manual verification steps.","The review notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."]'::jsonb),
